      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed via power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al. modified by Heuser-Opitz). NIH is the regulatory-recognized metric for hemolysis assessment per ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance on pump hemolysis testing. Secondary QoI is volume-averaged scalar shear stress. Both QoIs directly address the COU decision question regarding worst-case hemolysis. Gradation 2 achieved."
