      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB range (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM), covering all 5 flow-speed combinations in the COU. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, 40% hematocrit equivalent viscosity) used in PIV; bovine blood used for NIH validation. Spatial and temporal scales of validation match COU. Gradation 2 satisfied."
